entries.femaleVariant: It's... it's all so alive. So real.
Cyberspace moves, breathes at all times.
De interface will adjust de ebb and flow of data to de capabilities of your brain.
But you... you are an exceptional case.
So – what now?
We can begin. All is ready.
We enhanced your link to Silverhand's neural network for a short time. To grab de fragment.
We must find de data on Alt. Alt alone.
Dis should only take...
Yes. We extract de necessary fragment of Silverhand's engram.
We are ready now to make contact with Alt.
So, you don't actually know what's on the other side.
I held up my end of our deal. Your turn.
Before you pass through that wall, I want Johnny's psyche removed.
We will not pass through.
We take you into de cyberspace. No better place for you to interact with de construct.
Tell me why you want Johnny first.
How do I know I'll come back?
What's your plan to contact Alt?
How do I know I'll come back? Do I get some guarantee?
You will be inside our data fortress, under watch.
If you knew what is out there in de cyberspace, you would not be so choosy.
Under YOUR watch.
How's this any different from regular netrunning?
How's all this any different from plain ol' netrunning?
De interface show you de data layers direct from de Net. Readable, of course.
What de basic 'runners see is only a map. They cannot see beneath de surface. Their tech, it is too weak.
We try to cut out a unique piece of Silverhand's engram from de biochip.
Alt will know it. If something of de human is left after years beyond de Blackwall, she will answer.
Johnny? Looks like you're the bait. You OK with that?
Yeah, whatever. Just do what she says.
What do you want from Alt?
What exactly do you want from Alt? All of you?
When de Blackwall was built, everyone think de ICE would be enough, keep de wild AIs out, away.
This is our BBS. Data fortress.
Bridge to de deep Net.
Beyond, dere are no borders.
Beyond de Blackwall.
What's the Blackwall, really?
The Blackwall – what is it, exactly? I mean, I know…
entries.maleVariant: The Blackwall – what is it, exactly? I mean, I know...

entries.femaleVariant: You know only what de NetWatch tell you.
De final bastion against de postwar AIs. De great victory of humanity over chaos.
But de Blackwall is an AI itself. De boundary condition let no thing pass through, either way.
If de AIs thought like people, dey would call it a traitor.
That would be your Saturday morning NetWatch propaganda.
But technology advances, it cannot be stopped. And now, catastrophe come again. This is sure. And soon.
Alt de only one can give us safe passage past de Blackwall.
The change?
When de change come, we wish to be on de winning side.
And none have yet returned.
Few have gone through to de other side.
She will be de first.
De corporations, dey do not see de danger. But we – we will be ready.
Don't tell me I gotta get in that.
Oh, come on. Not the tub.
We must prepare you for de dive into cyberspace.
You are not accustomed to de neural demand.
Don't try an' get outta this, V. Just do what she says. I'm not about to sizzle with you.
Ooooh...
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Vire kouran." t="Turn on the power." b="" a=""/>
Before you cross the Blackwall, remove the construct.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Tout bagay pare. Nou ka kòmanse." t="Everything is ready. We can begin." b="" a=""/>
Looks like you're the bait.
Here.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Bon." t="Good." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Li pare." t="She's ready." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="creo" o="Li pare." t=" He's ready." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: [Get in] I'm ready.
Let's do this.
Where are we?
OK, wha… what now?
OK, what now?
Johnny?
J-Johnny?
This is it? Seriously?
This is it? Seriously?
Where are we?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Pare plonje." t="Ready to plunge." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ki moun ki pral pwoteje li?" t="Who will protect her?" b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="creo" o="Ki moun ki pral pwoteje li?" t="Who will protect him?" b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="creo" o="Leon avec Jean-ki-ri." t="Leon and Jean-ki-ri." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Direksyon konekte." t="Linking flows." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Koneksyon estab." t="Stable connection." b="" a=""/>
Must have your own version of a SynthTech interface.
OK, hang on. Wanna know what you need Silverhand for first.
entries.maleVariant: OK, hang on. I wanna know what you need Silverhand for first.

entries.femaleVariant: We wish to contact Alt Cunningham. We know she and Silverhand were close.
Alt?
The Relic which Arasaka held close, it is our only lead.
Alt Cunningham… heard of 'er.
Oh? Where, from who?
Alt – how do we contact her?
Johnny told me about her.
From Johnny. Though granted, not much.
Johnny?
All right, V. Guess you better tell 'er.
Tell her what?
About us.
How we contacting Alt?
Johnny's construct is active.
Construct's active. Lets me and Johnny shoot the shit every now and then.
Whoa, what? Said nothin' 'bout breakin' through the Blackwall.
entries.maleVariant: Whoa, what? You said nothin' 'bout breakin' through the Blackwall.

entries.femaleVariant: Well, now you know.
What, think I'm hallucinating? Found myself an imaginary friend?
Mhm. We will look at dis, too.
Little is known of how an engram might exist within a human's neural network.
Tell ya one thing – doesn't shake out well for the human.
Guess all this means you got your own SynthTech interface.
We have our own versions of all. We do not use anything from de city.
What the hell's goin' on?!
Dey breached our BBSes. We have nothing to do wid dis!
Joris, we must pull out!
Secure--!
Construct – what kinda shape's it in?
Enough data is uncorrupted to convince Alt it is authentic.
What the hell's that mean?
Alt…? Wh-what's goin' on?
Why you wait? De ice will melt waiting for your decision.
...a moment.
Did it work?
Felt like more than a moment.
Sure felt like more than a moment.
So... did it work?
Saw a good chunk of Johnny's life... And Alt.
It is possible. Data connected to Alt are linked to a strong memory trace in de construct. Very strong.
These memories must have evoked a powerful emotional response, then projected onto your consciousness.
Emotion, yeah, plenty of that...
What now?
It all seems so... alive.
Seein' somethin' more than I am?
<mothertongue l="creo" m="twò bèl" b="Yes. De cyberspace, it is always... " a="."/>
First, we must dive deeper.
What the construct's condition?
Fine. Not like I have a choice.
Don't got much for options, do I?
Should've guessed…
So actually… you got no idea what's beyond that thing.
entries.maleVariant: So actually… you've got no idea what's beyond that thing.

entries.femaleVariant: But we will know soon.
And these shapes I'm seein'…
Wild, unfettered AI. Searching for a passage.
You will take de code to de other side.
Fuck... Might've guessed.
Never had any intention of helpin' me, did ya?
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ale." t="Go." b="" a=""/>
[Touch] How do I cross over?
How do I get to the other side?
Brigitte?
It does not matter anymore.
You will bring all to its end.
Alt?
Alt?
Johnny.
You cannot remain here.
Alt Cunningham.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Joris! Rezo a gen plis chaj ..." t="Joris! The network's experiencing additional load…" b="" a=""/>
NetWatch.
W-what...?
What... is this?
What's happening?
Brigitte...?
[Grab]
